This analysis detects suspicious allocation size calculations for pointer arrays.
1. What expression computes the allocation size?
2. Is sizeof(pointer) used where sizeof(pointed-to type) is required?
3. What is the required size for the later writes/initialization operations?
4. Can this mismatch lead to out-of-bounds writes for realistic input sizes?
Use the tools to compare allocated byte count versus actual element usage.
If allocated size is sufficient for all writes, there is no issue.
Only flag if the allocation can be genuinely undersized at runtime.
